A TEENAGER whose body was found in the River Clyde has been identified by police. Body found in Clyde is identified as missing Gorbals teenager A TEENAGER whose body was found in the River Clyde has been identified by police.The body of Steven Clark, 17, was found on Monday night in Glasgow city centre.The teenager, from the Gorbals area, had been reported missing after being spotted &shy;going into the water last week.Underwater search teams had been looking for his body after he was last seen near the footbridge at Carlton Place, in Glasgow city centre. 